<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>PDO supports a connection attribute to perform case-folding by a few different policies.  The PDO attribute ATTR_CASE can have values:</p>

<ul><li>CASE_LOWER - fold identifiers to all lowercase when returning result sets in FETCH_ASSOC or FETCH_BOTH modes.</li>
<li>CASE_UPPER - fold identifiers to all uppercase when returning result sets in FETCH_ASSOC or FETCH_BOTH modes.</li>
<li>CASE_NATURAL - do not fold case of identifiers; use the exact spelling that the RDBMS returns.</li>
</ul><p>This is a feature request to permit the Adapter class to take an option in the constructor options.</p>

<p>If the Adapter is a PDO adapter, make this option cascade to set the corresponding PDO attribute in the underlying PDO connection object.</p>

<p>For non-PDO adapters, please implement matching behavior.</p>

<p>It is suggested that the option key be named simply "case", and the values match the existing const definitions Zend_Db::CASE_LOWER, Zend_Db::CASE_UPPER, and Zend_Db::CASE_NATURAL.  The values of these consts are identical to the consts of the same name in PDO.</p>

<p>Please make the default value in all adapters CASE_NATURAL.</p>

